reviewText: from watching some of her other work,I call riisa the "lady of 10000 faces. she runs through a full gambit of emotions for this story of a pregnant lady who goes to a southern island (near Okinawa?) to have her child. riisa is excellent in this role. the other actors are a step down, except a lady who acts as a Vietnamese import into the maternity clinic, who has a small supporting role fulfilled to perfection.
